{"ts":"2026-06-26T16:35:26.301Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Examining Layout Blocks**\n\nI'm impressed! The layout blocks are premium and align well with the landing page theme. I've shifted focus to other tool pages to maintain consistency and quality. Specifically, I'm checking `app/build/blueprint/page.tsx`, `app/build/assessment/page.tsx`, and `app/build/roi` for a consistent experience.\n\n\n**Designing Wizard Systems**\n\nI'm now consumed with designing a reusable wizard/stepper. The goal is a premium, custom experience for several tools. I'm focusing on features: step labels, progress indicators, accessibility, validation, and mobile optimization. I'm avoiding generic UI and leaning into the existing theme with tasteful motion, clear hierarchy, and mobile-friendly interactions. I intend to use Framer Motion only if present and to respect user preferences for reduced motion. The key is local-only reset, no backend calls, and wiring the system.\n\n\n**Constructing Wizard Component**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in the `WizardStepperSystem` component, aiming for a robust, premium experience. I've defined its core props: `steps`, `initialData`, `summaryItems`, `children` (with options for render props), `onComplete`, `renderResult`, and an optional `compilingMessages` array. I'm focusing on providing flexible options to control behavior while maintaining a good user experience. I'm aiming for flexibility, ease of use, and a delightful user experience. I will test these. I'm building from `components/build/WizardStepperSystem.tsx`.\n\n\n**Refactoring Wizard Structure**\n\nI'm now digging into the current structures of the existing tools to prepare for refactoring. I'm taking a close look at `app/build/blueprint/page.tsx`, specifically, to see how to integrate the new `WizardStepperSystem` seamlessly. My goal is to use this component across all five tools, ensuring a consistent and premium experience. I need to understand how best to restructure existing code to support this. I'm also preparing to show a premium animated compiling state using compiled step messages.\n\n\n**Integrating Wizard System**\n\nI'm now incredibly excited! I realize that refactoring the tools can provide a consistent multi-step flow. Assessment, ROI, Proposal, and Talk pages can all become wizard-driven, creating premium flows. Even better, I can maintain existing single-page tools. This is the correct path forward!\n\n\n**Planning Wizard Narrative**\n\nI'm now detailing the internal design plan for the `WizardStepperSystem`, focusing on a compelling narrative. I've landed on \"The Build Pipeline\" metaphor, where each step represents a configuration gate in an \"Enterprise Build Pipeline.\" This framing aims for a premium and engaging experience that stands out from a standard questionnaire. The sidebar becomes a pipeline controller, compiling live configuration variables, culminating in a \"Sovereign Compile\" sequence.\n\n\n**Defining Visual Design**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in the visual narrative. I'm focusing on a high-tech, single-tenant VPC telemetry interface with a dark, premium theme. I'm prioritizing laser-thin borders and dynamic glowing LEDs, emerald for passed validations, neon blue for active states. I am focused on a \"Variable Manifest\" summary panel and a compiling terminal console that mimics code compilation and dry-run traces.\n\nI'm also focusing on layout, now. Specifically, I'm employing a 12-column grid system matching the site theme. The left side (4 columns desktop, top mobile) is the \"Pipeline Controller & Live Manifest\" sidebar. It houses a track bar, interactive stepper list, and the \"Live Manifest.\" The right side (8 columns desktop, bottom mobile) is the \"Configuration Gate\" workspace for form fields.\n\n\n**Finalizing Interface Details**\n\nI'm now implementing the final touches. I'm focusing on a banner at the bottom that is aria-live enabled with a glowing crimson accent for accessibility. Next buttons have pulse effects. I'm also now designing a full-width \"Synthesis Console\" result, complete with graphs and export actions, after the compilation.\n\n**Implementing Interaction Strategy**\n\nI'm now detailing the interaction strategy. Smooth, horizontal slide animations are implemented, respecting user preferences for reduced motion with Tailwind. I'm also adding a live summary manifest that dynamically updates in the sidebar with subtle glows, and accessible keyboard navigations for submitting and going back/resetting steps. I'm focusing on the \"Sovereign Compile Sequence\" with realistic console outputs.\n\n**Addressing Mobile Strategy**\n\nI'm now detailing the mobile implementation. On mobile, the left sidebar stacks above the content gate. The sidebar collapses into a sticky \"Progress Bar & Manifest Summary Dropdown\" to avoid blocking form fields.\n\n\n"}}
